This is a known breaking change. In .NET 10, MAUI adopted Android's **edge-to-edge** mode by default, which makes `adjustResize` a no-op. The fix is to react to **keyboard window insets** instead.

### Solution: Listen to IME insets and adjust page padding

In your `ChatPage.xaml.cs` (or wherever you build the page), add a platform-specific inset listener:

```csharp
// ChatPage.xaml.cs
protected override void OnAppearing()
{
    base.OnAppearing();
#if ANDROID
    RegisterKeyboardInsetHandler();
#endif
}

#if ANDROID
void RegisterKeyboardInsetHandler()
{
    var activity = Platform.CurrentActivity;
    var rootView = activity?.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content);
    if (rootView is null) return;

    AndroidX.Core.View.ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
        rootView, new KeyboardInsetsListener(this));
}

class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object,
    AndroidX.Core.View.IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    readonly Page _page;
    public KeyboardInsetsListener(Page page) => _page = page;

    public AndroidX.Core.View.WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(
        Android.Views.View v, AndroidX.Core.View.WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var ime = insets.GetInsets(AndroidX.Core.View.WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var bars = insets.GetInsets(AndroidX.Core.View.WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());

        // Subtract the nav-bar height so you don't double-pad
        var bottomPx = Math.Max(ime.Bottom - bars.Bottom, 0);
        var bottomDip = bottomPx / DeviceDisplay.MainDisplayInfo.Density;

        _page.Padding = new Thickness(0, 0, 0, bottomDip);
        return insets;
    }
}
#endif
```

### Why this works

| .NET 9 (old) | .NET 10 (new) |
|---|---|
| `adjustResize` shrinks the window | Edge-to-edge: window stays full-screen |
| OS resizes your layout | You respond to `WindowInsets.Ime` yourself |

The listener fires whenever the keyboard opens or closes, and you shift your entire page up by setting bottom `Padding` equal to the keyboard height.

### Tips for a chat screen

- Put messages in a `CollectionView` (row 0) and input bar in a `Grid` row with `Auto` height (row 1) — the padding pushes everything up together.
- If you also use `SafeAreaPadding`, merge it with the keyboard padding so they don't conflict.
- Remove any old `UseWindowSoftInputModeAdjust` calls — they're obsolete and will produce build warnings.
